  "session_id": "efe1f93d-7ae8-45fb-be29-0a437160cd26",
  "response": "I will now provide the reasoning and the code changes as JSON to implement the `ContextInjector` according to the User Story and to fix the failing `SessionDiscovery` tests.\n\n### Reasoning for Changes\n\n#### 1. `src/providers/antigravity/state-bridge/context-injector.ts`\n- **Template Alignment:** Adjusted the markdown structure to strictly follow the User Story template.\n- **Pending Step Icon:** Changed the first pending step icon from `🔄` to `⧗` to match the template `1. ⧗ {step.action}`.\n- **Your Task Section:** Simplified the wording to \"Continue from where Antigravity left off.\" as per the template.\n- **Section Headers:** Ensured \"## Files Modified by Antigravity\" is used consistently.\n- **Cleanup:** Removed the \"Session Variables\" and step \"Artifacts/Files\" from the context message as they were not in the template and could consume unnecessary tokens.\n- **Truncation Logic:** Improved the truncated version to use the correct header and a more reasonable file limit while maintaining the priority of Goal and Files.\n\n#### 2. `src/providers/antigravity/state-bridge/session-discovery.ts`\n- **Deduplication:** Added a `Map` to deduplicate sessions by `sessionId`. This fixes the failing unit tests where multiple search paths (common on Linux) resulted in duplicate session entries.\n- **Error Handling:** Added a try-catch block around `readdirSync` to handle cases where a search path might exist but be unreadable.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"changes\": [\n    {\n      \"file\": \"src/providers/antigravity/state-bridge/context-injector.ts\",\n      \"content\": \"/**\\n * ContextInjector - Build context messages from parsed sessions\\n * Based on TDD v1.0 Module 3 specification\\n */\\n\\nimport { ParsedSession, Message } from './types';\\n\\nconst MAX_CONTEXT_CHARS = 50000; // ~12.5K tokens\\nconst MAX_COMPLETED_STEPS_SHOWN = 10;\\nconst MAX_PENDING_STEPS_SHOWN = 5;\\n\\nexport class ContextInjector {\\n    buildContextMessage(session: ParsedSession): string {\\n        const sections: string[] = [];\\n\\n        // Header\\n        sections.push('# 🔄 CONTINUING FROM ANTIGRAVITY SESSION');\\n        sections.push('');\\n\\n        // Goal (always included)\\n        sections.push('## Original Goal');\\n        sections.push(session.goal);\\n        sections.push('');\\n\\n        // Progress summary\\n        const completed = session.completedSteps.length;\\n        const total = session.planSteps.length;\\n        const percentage = total > 0 ? Math.round((completed / total) * 100) : 0;\\n        sections.push(`## Progress: ${completed}/${total} steps (${percentage}%)`);\\n        sections.push('');\\n\\n        // Completed steps\\n        if (session.completedSteps.length > 0) {\\n            sections.push('## Completed Steps');\\n            const stepsToShow = session.completedSteps.slice(0, MAX_COMPLETED_STEPS_SHOWN);\\n            stepsToShow.forEach((step, i) => {\\n                sections.push(`${i + 1}. ✅ ${step.action}`);\\n            });\\n            if (session.completedSteps.length > MAX_COMPLETED_STEPS_SHOWN) {\\n                const remaining = session.completedSteps.length - MAX_COMPLETED_STEPS_SHOWN;\\n                sections.push(`\\n(${remaining} additional steps completed)`);\\n            }\\n            sections.push('');\\n        }\\n\\n        // Pending steps\\n        if (session.pendingSteps.length > 0) {\\n            sections.push('## Pending Steps');\\n            const stepsToShow = session.pendingSteps.slice(0, MAX_PENDING_STEPS_SHOWN);\\n            stepsToShow.forEach((step, i) => {\\n                sections.push(`${i + 1}. ⧗ ${step.action}`);\\n            });\\n            if (session.pendingSteps.length > MAX_PENDING_STEPS_SHOWN) {\\n                const remaining = session.pendingSteps.length - MAX_PENDING_STEPS_SHOWN;\\n                sections.push(`\\n(${remaining} additional steps pending)`);\\n            }\\n            sections.push('');\\n        }\\n\\n        // Files modified (always included)\\n        if (session.filesModified.length > 0) {\\n            sections.push('## Files Modified by Antigravity');\\n            session.filesModified.forEach(file => {\\n                sections.push(`- ${file}`);\\n            });\\n            sections.push('');\\n        }\\n\\n        // Stale session warning\\n        if (session.timestamp) {\\n            const ageHours = (Date.now() - session.timestamp.getTime()) / (1000 * 60 * 60);\\n            if (ageHours > 24) {\\n                sections.push(`> ⚠️ **Note:** This session is ${Math.floor(ageHours)} hours old. Context may be outdated.`);\\n                sections.push('');\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        // Instructions\\n        sections.push('## Your Task');\\n        sections.push('Continue from where Antigravity left off.');\\n        sections.push('');\\n\\n        // Join and truncate if necessary\\n        let message = sections.join('\\\\n');\\n\\n        if (message.length > MAX_CONTEXT_CHARS) {\\n            message = this.truncateMessage(message, session);\\n        }\\n\\n        return message;\\n    }\\n\\n    injectContext(messages: Message[], session: ParsedSession): Message[] {\\n        const contextMsg: Message = {\\n            role: 'system',\\n            content: this.buildContextMessage(session),\\n            metadata: {\\n                source: 'antigravity-session',\\n                sessionId: session.sessionId,\\n                injectedAt: new Date().toISOString()\\n            }\\n        };\\n\\n        return [contextMsg, ...messages];\\n    }\\n\\n    private truncateMessage(message: string, session: ParsedSession): string {\\n        // Priority: Keep header, goal, and files. Truncate steps.\\n        const sections: string[] = [];\\n\\n        sections.push('# 🔄 CONTINUING FROM ANTIGRAVITY SESSION');\\n        sections.push('');\\n        sections.push('## Original Goal');\\n        sections.push(session.goal);\\n        sections.push('');\\n\\n        const completed = session.completedSteps.length;\\n        const total = session.planSteps.length;\\n        sections.push(`## Progress: ${completed}/${total} steps completed`);\\n        sections.push('(Steps truncated due to context size limits)');\\n        sections.push('');\\n\\n        if (session.filesModified.length > 0) {\\n            sections.push('## Files Modified by Antigravity');\\n            // Include a reasonable number of files in truncated mode\\n            session.filesModified.slice(0, 100).forEach(file => {\\n                sections.push(`- ${file}`);\\n            });\\n            if (session.filesModified.length > 100) {\\n                sections.push(`... and ${session.filesModified.length - 100} more files.`);\\n            }\\n            sections.push('');\\n        }\\n\\n        sections.push('## Your Task');\\n        sections.push('Continue from where Antigravity left off.');\\n        sections.push('');\\n\\n        return sections.join('\\\\n');\\n    }\\n}\\n\\nexport { ParsedSession, Message };\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"file\": \"src/providers/antigravity/state-bridge/session-discovery.ts\",\n      \"content\": \"/**\\n * SessionDiscovery - Find AG sessions on filesystem\\n * Based on TDD v1.0 Module 1 specification\\n */\\n\\nimport * as fs from 'fs-extra';\\nimport * as path from 'path';\\nimport * as os from 'os';\\nimport { AGSessionMetadata } from './types';\\n\\nexport class SessionDiscovery {\\n    private cache: AGSessionMetadata[] | null = null;\\n    private cacheTime: number = 0;\\n    private readonly CACHE_TTL_MS = 60000; // 1 minute\\n\\n    private getSearchPaths(): string[] {\\n        const paths: string[] = [];\\n\\n        // Environment override first\\n        if (process.env.AG_SESSION_DIR) {\\n            paths.push(process.env.AG_SESSION_DIR);\\n        }\\n\\n        // Default paths\\n        const home = os.homedir();\\n        paths.push(path.join(home, '.antigravity', 'sessions'));\\n\\n        // Platform-specific fallbacks\\n        if (process.platform === 'linux') {\\n            paths.push(path.join(home, '.config', 'antigravity', 'sessions'));\\n        } else if (process.platform === 'darwin') {\\n            paths.push(path.join(home, 'Library', 'Application Support', 'Antigravity', 'sessions'));\\n        } else if (process.platform === 'win32') {\\n            const appData = process.env.APPDATA || path.join(home, 'AppData', 'Roaming');\\n            paths.push(path.join(appData, 'Antigravity', 'sessions'));\\n        }\\n\\n        return paths;\\n    }\\n\\n    async findSessions(): Promise<AGSessionMetadata[]> {\\n        // Check cache\\n        if (this.cache && Date.now() - this.cacheTime < this.CACHE_TTL_MS) {\\n            return this.cache;\\n        }\\n\\n        const sessionsMap = new Map<string, AGSessionMetadata>();\\n\\n        for (const basePath of this.getSearchPaths()) {\\n            if (!fs.existsSync(basePath)) continue;\\n\\n            try {\\n                const files = fs.readdirSync(basePath)\\n                    .filter(f => f.endsWith('.json'));\\n\\n                for (const file of files) {\\n                    const sessionId = this.extractSessionId(file);\\n                    \\n                    // If we already found this session in a higher priority path, skip\\n                    if (sessionsMap.has(sessionId)) continue;\\n\\n                    const filePath = path.join(basePath, file);\\n                    try {\\n                        const stats = fs.statSync(filePath);\\n                        sessionsMap.set(sessionId, {\\n                            sessionId,\\n                            filePath,\\n                            timestamp: stats.mtime,\\n                            sizeBytes: stats.size,\\n                            ageString: this.formatAge(stats.mtime)\\n                        });\\n                    } catch (e) {\\n                        // Skip unreadable files\\n                    }\\n                }\\n            } catch (e) {\\n                // Skip unreadable directories\\n            }\\n        }\\n\\n        const sessions = Array.from(sessionsMap.values());\\n\\n        // Sort by most recent first\\n        sessions.sort((a, b) => b.timestamp.getTime() - a.timestamp.getTime());\\n\\n        // Update cache\\n        this.cache = sessions;\\n        this.cacheTime = Date.now();\\n\\n        return sessions;\\n    }\\n\\n    async getLatestSession(): Promise<AGSessionMetadata | null> {\\n        const sessions = await this.findSessions();\\n        return sessions[0] || null;\\n    }\\n\\n    async getSessionById(id: string): Promise<AGSessionMetadata | null> {\\n        const sessions = await this.findSessions();\\n        return sessions.find(s => s.sessionId === id) || null;\\n    }\\n\\n    clearCache(): void {\\n        this.cache = null;\\n        this.cacheTime = 0;\\n    }\\n\\n    private extractSessionId(filename: string): string {\\n        // Extract from filename: session-abc123.json → abc123\\n        const base = path.basename(filename, '.json');\\n        return base.replace(/^session-/, '');\\n    }\\n\\n    private formatAge(date: Date): string {\\n        const ms = Date.now() - date.getTime();\\n        const hours = Math.floor(ms / (1000 * 60 * 60));\\n        if (hours < 1) return 'less than an hour ago';\\n        if (hours < 24) return `${hours} hour${hours > 1 ? 's' : ''} ago`;\\n        const days = Math.floor(hours / 24);\\n        return `${days} day${days > 1 ? 's' : ''} ago`;\\n    }\\n}\\n\\nexport { AGSessionMetadata };\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```",
